To use the new certificate, you have two different options:

- Use the internal ingress chart support (example [ingress wordpress section](https://github.com/bitnami/charts/tree/master/bitnami/wordpress#ingress)).

To configure the ingress to work with Cert Manager in Wordpress, for example:

Just enable the key ingress.certManager and include inside the ingress annotations:

~~~
kubernetes.io/ingress.class: nginx
cert-manager.io/cluster-issuer: letsencrypt-prod
~~~

- Create your own ingress, here you can find an example:

~~~
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: bitnami-ingress-test
  annotations:
    kubernetes.io/ingress.class: "nginx"
    cert-manager.io/issuer: "letsencrypt-prod"
spec:
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - bitnami.com
    secretName: letencrypt-ca
  rules:
  - host: bitnami.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: Exact
        backend:
          service:
            name: bitnami-ingress-test
            port:
              number: 80
~~~
